  <sections xmi:id="_Tdv4cP3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ" name="Determine the Scope of the Metrics to Capture" guid="_Tdv4cP3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ">
    <sectionDescription>The metrics may be captured for a given project,&amp;nbsp;a community, or for the entire enterprise.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_YFPA8P3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ" name="Determine the Recipients of the Metrics to Capture" guid="_YFPA8P3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The target individuals, or teams, who will be receiving the metrics should be identified. For example the target&#xD;
    individuals may be a project leader, or may be the Sponsor.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_e3v2kP3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ" name="Determine Frequency of Capturing Metrics" guid="_e3v2kP3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ">
    <sectionDescription>Some metrics may be captured more easily from the repository whereas other metrics may require some digging and calculation&#xD;
work. In this step the manager determines how is gathering the metrics, and what will they need to do in order to collect&#xD;
them.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_jvx8gP3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ" name="Determine Who Will Capture the Metrics and How" guid="_jvx8gP3TEdubna2vE0o6gQ">
    <sectionDescription>Some metrics may be captured more easily from the repository, whereas other metrics may require some digging and&#xD;
calculation work. In this step, the manager determines who is gathering the metrics, and what they will&amp;nbsp;need to do in&#xD;
order to collect them.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
